#: home/templates/articles/cr/article_0001.html:4
#: home/templates/articles/cr/article_0001.html:7
#: home/templates/articles/cr/article_0001.html:10
msgid "How to Run Payroll in Costa Rica | ExactusPay"
msgstr "Comment gérer la paie au Costa Rica | ExactusPay"

#: home/templates/articles/cr/article_0001.html:5
#: home/templates/articles/cr/article_0001.html:8
#: home/templates/articles/cr/article_0001.html:11
msgid ""
"A practical guide to payroll setup and employer obligations in Costa Rica, "
"including social security, reporting discipline, and payroll operating "
"controls."
msgstr ""

#: home/templates/articles/cr/article_0001.html:12
msgid "How to run payroll in Costa Rica with stronger control from day one"
msgstr ""
"Comment exécuter la paie au Costa Rica avec plus de contrôle dès le premier "
"jour"

#: home/templates/articles/cr/article_0001.html:13
msgid ""
"Costa Rica payroll requires a reliable local process for contributions, "
"filings, employee records, and supporting evidence. The easiest way to keep "
"control is to standardise the payroll operating model before volume grows."
msgstr ""

#: home/templates/articles/cr/article_0001.html:17
msgid "Entity readiness"
msgstr "Préparation de l'entité"

#: home/templates/articles/cr/article_0001.html:18
msgid ""
"Confirm the employing structure, registrations, and operating "
"responsibilities before onboarding employees."
msgstr ""

#: home/templates/articles/cr/article_0001.html:21
msgid "Payroll discipline"
msgstr "Discipline paie"

#: home/templates/articles/cr/article_0001.html:22
msgid ""
"Treat payroll as a controlled process with validated inputs, approvals, and "
"statutory outputs."
msgstr ""

#: home/templates/articles/cr/article_0001.html:25
msgid "Regional scale"
msgstr "Expertise régionale"

#: home/templates/articles/cr/article_0001.html:26
msgid "Translate local outputs into one reporting standard across LATAM."
msgstr ""
"Traduisez les résultats locaux dans un standard unique de reporting pour "
"l'Amérique latine."

#: home/templates/articles/cr/article_0001.html:31
msgid "1. Start with the local operating model"
msgstr "1. Commencer par le modèle opérationnel local"

#: home/templates/articles/cr/article_0001.html:32
msgid ""
"Before the first payroll cycle, identify who owns local registrations, "
"payroll processing, approvals, and statutory remittances. Those ownership "
"boundaries matter more than they appear at the start."
msgstr ""

#: home/templates/articles/cr/article_0001.html:35
msgid "2. Protect payroll quality with stronger input controls"
msgstr ""
"2. Protégez la qualité de la paie grâce à des contrôles de saisie renforcés"

#: home/templates/articles/cr/article_0001.html:36
msgid ""
"Compensation changes, new hires, leave, and terminations should move through "
"one documented process. When inputs arrive late or without approval, payroll "
"teams lose time to manual corrections and finance loses confidence in the "
"numbers."
msgstr ""

#: home/templates/articles/cr/article_0001.html:39
msgid "3. Report Costa Rica in the same language as the rest of the group"
msgstr "3. Présentez le Costa Rica dans la même langue que le reste du groupe"

#: home/templates/articles/cr/article_0001.html:40
msgid ""
"A local provider may produce local-format outputs, but headquarters still "
"needs clean, comparable payroll visibility. A shared reporting model is what "
"turns local execution into regional control."
msgstr ""

